job_history.work_description: To drive business initiatives by providing strategic HR guidance to leadership and management through planning, organizing and controlling the activities of the Human Resources Department.
Effectively work with management and hourly base to develop programs and strategies that create an employer of choice environment and make unionization obsolete.
Source and engage clients to develop and implement staffing strategies to drive business goals.
Responsible for recruitment, selection, training and development of management/exempt level personnel.
80% travel among 21 matrixed facilities, establishing recruitment processes and practices that generated results.
Responsible for guiding team of HR professionals dedicated to selecting qualified candidates to work at various client locations.
Managed 24hr location. Generated $13 million in sales annually, supervising and motivating 46 employees.
